Package com.bakdata.dedupe.deduplication.online

Interface OnlineDeduplication<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Deduplication<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FusingOnlineDuplicateDetection
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
    @FunctionalInterface
public interface OnlineDeduplication<T>
extends Deduplication<T>
    A full online deduplication process, which ensures that no duplicate record is emitted.

    Consider a stream of records A, B, A' and A, A' being duplicates. The resulting stream will be A, B, A", where A" is a suitable representation of A and A'.

    The actual implementation may use any means necessary to find duplicates, to ensure proper transitivity ((A,B) is duplicate and (B,C) is duplicate implies that (A,C) is duplicate), and to give a resulting representation.

    Implementation Requirements:
    It is assumed that any duplicate A' of a previous value A results in a returned representation with the same identifier as A. Implementations should document under which conditions this assumptions holds.

      • deduplicate

        @NonNull
T deduplicate​(@NonNull
              T newRecord)
        Deduplicates the record with all previously seen records.

        There are two cases:

        • No duplicate has been detected: The record itself is returned.
        • At least one duplicate has been detected: The record is added to the duplicate Cluster and a suitable representation for that cluster is returned.
        Parameters:
        newRecord - the record that should be processed with all previously seen records
        Returns:
        the record or a representation of the duplicate Cluster of the record.

        Deduplicates the dataset.

        Note that for online algorithms, duplicates will be repeatedly emitted with updated representation, since it is impossible to suppress earlier emission without blocking execution. The user needs to invalidate earlier results through external means (for example, putting them in a key-value store with the key being the id of the duplicate).
